 pip3 --version
 pip3 install pipenv
 pipenv install django
 
 cd /root/.local/share/virtualenvs/backend-b5mj06XY     --> created the virtual env
 
 pipenv shell  --> For activate the python virtual env. --> to run this command on the manage.py file location **** [NOTE]
 
 django-admin startproject test1   ---> create an test1 django project
 
 django-admin startproject test1 .  --> it will assigin current directory as a core directory
 
 python manage.py migrate
  
  
  put a host entry on settings.py -->  ALLOWED_HOSTS = ['192.168.5.10']
  
 python manage.py runserver --> to run the server default port 8000

or

python manage.py runserver 192.168.5.10:9000 ---> now it will run the port 9000


python manage.py startapp testapp --> create an app



